race.description: Ladbrokes Racing Extras In Multi Class 3 Handicap
race.comment: Liked the run of ELLIBABY (7) fresh in city class when she found the line well for a close-up fourth. Well placed here and fitter again should go close. BOOM SHOT (3) was midfield in a hot form race two back then had no luck last time. Going better than form suggests and with clear running will be tough to stop this line-up. TORO STRIKE (6) has been thereabouts without winning, the latest when fifth over 1200m at this track two weeks ago, beaten 2.75 lengths. Ready to win and from four starts on rain affected going has a win and three minors. Gets chance to dire and looks a major player with any luck from the draw. HELL AND BACK (5) raced in easier company last start finished second at Gold Coast. Going well and loves the wet ground. Can give a sight.
